      <chapter id="508">
        <pagenum>2</pagenum>
        <subchapter>0</subchapter>
        <title>Activity:  Reading - the Strategies</title>
        <content>&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;In order to provide busy adults with the amount of practice required to develop skill expertise, adult educators must find ways to support student persistence and motivation.  From an extensive National Research Council  report, &lt;i&gt;Improving Adult Literacy Instruction:  Options for Practice and Research &lt;/i&gt;(2012) emerged a shorter publication, &lt;i&gt;Improving&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i&gt; Adult Literacy: Supporting Learning and Motivation. &lt;/i&gt;Chapter 3 of this booklet, which serves as the basis for this course reading, describes a set of 11 evidence-based strategies for shaping learning environments that build student motivation and their will to persist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;It’s important to keep in mind that the strategies interact in complex ways to influence learner motivation. For example, providing clear feedback can help students have an accurate sense of their abilities and set achievable goals and, conversely, having clear goals can help instructors focus on useful, relevant feedback.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;The &lt;a title="Highlights of Motivation and Persistence Strategies" href="$@PAGEVIEWBYID*5004@$" target="_blank"&gt;Highlights of Motivation and Persistence Strategies &lt;/a&gt;has descriptions excerpted from &lt;i&gt;Improving Adult Literacy Instruction: Supporting Learning and Motivation **&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;**Extended Learning Opportunity: Optional Reading&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;To view the strategies and explanations as a whole rather than as separate excerpts in the Highlights document, read Chapter 3 (pp. 13–24) from &lt;i&gt;Improving Adult Literacy: Supporting Learning and Motivation&lt;/i&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;Access this chapter by downloading the 32-page booklet from &lt;a title="Improving Adult Literacy Instruction" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Improving%20Adult%20Lit.%20Instruction.pdf" target="_blank"&gt;Improving Adult Literacy: Supporting Learning and Motivation (PDF)&lt;/a&gt;. [Reprinted with permission from the National Academy of Sciences, Courtesy of the National Academies Press, Washington, DC.]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
