        <title>Extended Learning Opportunity: Growth vs. Fixed Mindset (optional)</title>
        <content>&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Introduction: &lt;/b&gt;Self-efficacy is strongly affected by one’s beliefs about intelligence. According to Dr. Carol Dweck's research, some people believe that their intellectual ability is a fixed trait. You either have it or you don’t. People with a &lt;i&gt;fixed mindset&lt;/i&gt; tend to avoid challenging tasks because they fear that not doing well will reveal that they are not smart. By contrast, people with a &lt;i&gt;growth mindset&lt;/i&gt; believe that their intellectual ability is something they can develop through effort and education. For more on Dr. Dweck's research, see her article &lt;i&gt;&lt;a title="The Perils and Promise of Praise" href="http://www.ascd.org/publications/educational-leadership/oct07/vol65/num02/The-Perils-and-Promises-of-Praise.aspx" target="_blank"&gt;The Perils and Promises of Praise&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.ascd.org/publications/educational-leadership/oct07/vol65/num02/The-Perils-and-Promises-of-Praise.aspx"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Optional Activity: &lt;/b&gt;Note one way you think you might be sending a &lt;i&gt;fixed mindset&lt;/i&gt; message to your students, and one way you send a &lt;i&gt;growth mindset&lt;/i&gt; message. Use this &lt;a title="Changing the Message Chart" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ChangingMessagev2.docx" target="_blank"&gt;Changing the Message chart (Word)&lt;/a&gt; to help you reframe fixed mindset into growth mindset messages. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optional Reading:&lt;/strong&gt; Download the following ideas and more from Extended Learning Opportunity: &lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Voices_from_the_Field.pdf"&gt;Voices from the Field&lt;/a&gt; Optional Reading.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
